summary: #REBLOGGING THIS AGAIN BECAUSE I FORGOT TO MENTION#remember how it's a huge thing in kree culture#that you never tell ANYONE who...
body:
#REBLOGGING THIS AGAIN BECAUSE I FORGOT TO MENTION#remember how it’s a huge thing in kree culture#that you never tell ANYONE who you see when you visit the supreme intelligence??#AND SHE TOLD HIM?????#BECAUSE SHE TRUSTS HIM THAT MUCH????? (@jennathearcher​)

Yes, and even more amazing: She asks Yon-Rogg who he sees and even nags him about it.

Vers knows Yon-Rogg is the poster boy of the Kree. He’s been trying since six years to make her less emotional because that’s the Kree way of thinking/living.
She knows he’s really focused on following the rules and is pretty much exactly what the Kree aspire to be.
She knows the Kree never tell anyone who they see the Supreme Intelligence as because it’s so private to them.

Yet she asks. In fact, it’s literally her immediate reaction (”It’s personal. No Kree divulges it. Ever.” - “Who do you see?”). And she keeps guessing people when he refuses to answer. It’s obviously weird to her that he won’t tell her so she must be used to Yon-Rogg sharing everything with her, no matter how personal it is. And that’s beautiful.

(And she’s probably also used to him always giving in when she just annoys him enough which is why she keeps doing it. She rightfully never fears it will anger him because, as it’s shown in the film, it really just amuses him.)

summary:
Captain Marvel (2019) dir.

Anna Boden, Ryan Fleck. 7.4/10 About Vers trying to remember who she was but also trying to control...
caption:
Captain Marvel (2019) dir. Anna Boden, Ryan Fleck.
7.4/10

About Vers trying to remember who she was but also trying to control her powers. She’s trying to stop the war happening in outer space until she comes across where she once grew up and the secrets that led to her being here. 

I’m dead at goose on the plane. 

I like it when Brie Larson laughs. 

It was a good touch to add in the little kid so it can show women empowerment and also kid empowerment. 

I love how everything comes full circle. I wanna rewatch all of marvel. 

Memorable Quotes:
“Anger only serves the enemy.”

summary: Unpopular opinion. I think Rey from Star Wars is a horrible example of a strong female character. She is on the same level of...
question: Unpopular opinion. I think Rey from Star Wars is a horrible example of a strong female character. She is on the same level of Mary Sue crappy as say, Captain Marvel and is reviled by anyone outside the tumblr echochamber. I never for once believe their struggles and find them dull, unbelievable and unrelatable. If anything, she is an example of what not to do. Sorry... I guess this isn't really an ask.
answer:
Hello anon,

While you’re certainly entitled to your opinion, I think you are mistaken when you say that “Rey is  eviled by anyone outside the tumblr echochamber”.

I was at Star Wars Celebration this past April and there was a lot of love for Rey and I am sure that most of those people weren’t part of the “tumblr echo chamber”. 

Rey is an intrinsically good character, however, she’s also someone who is willing to an enemy when she believes that their path can be altered by her help. That doesn’t quite work out the way she wishes it did but nonetheless she’s someone who is willing to look past past conflicts. 

The same with Captain Marvel. It’s literally one of the top-grossing Marvel movies of all time. All the people who went to watch the films and who love and admire Captain Marvel are not part of the tumblr echo chamber. 

They might not be your preferred brand of heroines but they are heroines who inspire others and who others look to for comfort and belonging.

summary: When Vers finds the information about Dr. Lawson and figures that she must have had a life on Earth she’s obviously extremely...
body:
When Vers finds the information about Dr. Lawson and figures that she must have had a life on Earth she’s obviously extremely distressed. All of this is just overwhelming her, she feels lost and confused. So what is the next thing she does? Calling Yon-Rogg.

She’s not reporting anything to him, in fact she had even failed to follow his command. Yon-Rogg had told her to hold her position, to not leave the place she had called him from - an order Vers willingly ignored. Yet she knows exactly she can call him anyway because not following orders never had any real consequences for her and because he is her best friend and will be there for her no matter what. She trusts him. He’s her rock. Yon-Rogg had been there for her since she woke up on Hala and never changed during the six years they spend together. No matter the time or place, when Vers needed him, he was there. So naturally she immediately calls him to get his support.

He obviously doesn’t tell her the truth, can’t tell her the truth but he still tries to reassure her. What’s most important, however, is his diction.

The fact that he lied to her only hurts her so much because she would have never expected it. Yon-Rogg has always been her friend. It was always them against the world.They were a team, just the two of them. He never mistreated her or even has been even slightly mean to her in any way which is why his lie hits her so hard, why “He lied to me.” is the first thing she says after she learnt the truth and not something like “They lied to me.” or even “He killed Dr. Lawson.” She trusted Yon-Rogg because he never abused her and instead, even when you include the lie, has been the best and most supportive friend she ever had apart from Maria.

Yon-Rogg had told her to hold her position, to not leave the place she had called him from - an order Vers willingly ignored. Yet she knows exactly she can call him anyway because not following orders never had any real consequences for her and because he is her best friend and will be there for her no matter what. She trusts him. He’s her rock. Yon-Rogg had been there for her since she woke up on Hala and never changed during the six years they spend together. No matter the time or place, when Vers needed him, he was there. So naturally she immediately calls him to get his support.

He obviously doesn’t tell her the truth, can’t tell her the truth but he still tries to reassure her. What’s most important, however, is his diction.

The fact that he lied to her only hurts her so much because she would have never expected it. Yon-Rogg has always been her friend. It was always them against the world.They were a team, just the two of them. He never mistreated her or even has been even slightly mean to her in any way which is why his lie hits her so hard, why “He lied to me.” is the first thing she says after she learnt the truth and not something like “They lied to me.” or even “He killed Dr. Lawson.” She trusted Yon-Rogg because he never abused her and instead, even when you include the lie, has been the best and most supportive friend she ever had apart from Maria.
